ch hinsichtlich der deutschen Erinnerungskultur nach 1945 wertvolle Erkenntnisse liefert.  aThis work examines Gert Ledig’s depiction of the Second World War as a fundamentally traumatic event both on the front lines and in bombed out German cities. It focuses on how Ledig integrates war violence into his novels, and how he communicates this violence to readers. Extending the discussion to similar works and their reception, the author thus illuminates a hitherto neglected field of German post-war literature.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aGerman fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aViolence in literature. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xLiterature and the war. 4aBombenkrieg. 4aErinnerungskultur. 4aPosttraumatische Erkrankung. 4aWeltkrieg II/ i.d. Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh  aSecond World War/literature.  aculture of memory.  apost-traumatic illness.  astrategic bombing of Germany.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1z978311069627108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831106579370 cprintz978311065197340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311065712840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110657128423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110657128/original  a978-3-11-069627-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2020 Part 1b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2020  aZDB-23-DKUb2020